11/02/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- A non-binding resolution in the US Congress which describes the killings of Armenians in the Ottoman Empire during World War I as genocide could cause permanent damage to Turkish-US relations, Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said upon his return from Washington on Saturday (10 February). He added that President George Bush and Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice had warned the Congress of what he described as a "potential danger to US interests". 
In other news, three children hospitalized in Turkey with bird flu-like symptoms have tested negative for the disease. All came from the southeastern village of Bogazkoy. Turkey's Health Ministry confirmed that the dangerous H5N1 strain of the virus has been detected. All domestic fowl in the area have been culled in a bid to prevent the spread of the disease. (Reuters, AFP - 10/02/07)
